  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "To get admission into St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for a B.Com program, you typically need a strong academic record. While the exact cutoff percentage can vary from year to year, generally, you should aim for a minimum of 75-80% in your 12th board exams. \n\nHere are a few tips to increase your chances:\n\n1. **Check Previous Cutoffs:** Look at the previous years' cutoff percentages to get an idea of the competition.\n2. **Focus on Key Subjects:** Ensure you have good scores in subjects like Accountancy, Economics, and Mathematics, as these are often considered for B.Com admissions.\n3. **Prepare for Entrance Exams:** Some colleges may require you to take an entrance exam, so prepare accordingly if that's the case.\n4. **Extracurricular Activities:** Participating in extracurricular activities can sometimes give you an edge in the admission process.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check the latest admission criteria directly from the college website or by contacting the admissions office for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
